* Handle file names containing a newline
* Lock the backup directory to avoid races (eg: purge vs backup)
* Sort output of backup listing
* Split RX/TX stats by type (data vs metadata)
* Do stats even in dry-run mode
* Do not print stats everytime (eg: for the `list` command)
* --dry-run for the restore command
* --cache-dir (local cache for directory description files)

